body:
```
module M;
  wire [1:0] PIN;
  pullup(PIN[0]);
  pulldown(PIN[1]);
endmodule
```
reports
```
%Error-UNSUPPORTED: a.v:4:11: Unsupported: Conflicting pull directions.
                            : ... In instance M
    4 |   pulldown(PIN[1]);
      |           ^
                    a.v:3:9: ... Location of conflicting pull.
    3 |   pullup(PIN[0]);
      |         ^
                    ... For error description see https://verilator.org/warn/UNSUPPORTED?v=5.007

```
Appreciate it says UNSUPPORTED, but the message says that conflicting pull directions are unsupported, when there are no conflicting pull directions here as they are on different pins. Is it unsupported to pull a specific pin or range of pins?
